This paper deals with reinforcement learning in a non-rewarding environment, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a new unsupervised reinforcement learning agent called CLIC for Curriculum Learning and Imitation for Control. The paper also discusses the control of individual objects in the environment, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the imitation of Bob's interactions with objects, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the learning progress of the agent, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.SY, in that order.
